---
import Presentation from "../../../components/Presentation.astro";
import Divider from "../../../components/ui/Divider.astro";
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Code } from "astro-expressive-code/components";

//#region CodeSnippets
const Figure1 = `console.log(\`Pizza Hut > Dominos. Fight me.\`);`;
const Figure2 = `console.log("You scored", score, "%.");`;
const Figure3 = `console.log(\`You scored \${score}%.\`);`;
const Figure4 = `console.log(\`I am 35 years old, which is \${35 * 12} months.\`);`;
const Task1 = `let score = 95;

console.log("You scored", score, "%.");
console.log(\`You scored \${score}%.\`);
`;
const Task2 = `let score = 95;

console.log("You scored", score, "%.");
console.log(\`You scored \${score}%.\`);

let name = "Ada";
let age = 16;

console.log(\`\${name} is \${age} years old.\`);
`;
const Task3 = `let score = 95;

console.log("You scored", score, "%.");
console.log(\`You scored \${score}%.\`);

let name = "Ada";
let age = 16;

console.log(\`\${name} is \${age} years old.\`);

console.log(\`If I take out a $1000 loan, and pay $25 each month, I will pay it off in \${1000 / 25} months.\`);
console.log(\`A woodchuck could chuck \${32 * 60} wood panels every hour.\`);
`;
const SampleOutput = `You scored 95 %.
You scored 95%.
Ada is 16 years old.
If I take out a $1000 loan, and pay $25 each month, I will pay it off in 40 months.
A woodchuck could chuck 1920 wood panels every hour.`;
//#endregion
---

<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a href="/courses/ap-csp/" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3">
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Activity 1.6: String Interpolation</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-5" />

        <!-- Launch / Concept -->
        <section id="launch">
          <Presentation>
            <section>
              <h2>Activity 1.6</h2>
              <h3 class="text-sn-theme">String Interpolation</h3>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Concepts</h2>
              <p>Template Literals</p>
              <p>Interpolation</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>Backtick Strings</h2>
              <p>
                Strings can also be written with backticks
                (<code>`</code>) instead of quotes. On their own, they work
                exactly the same way.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure1} frame="code" lang="javascript" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>The Problem</h2>
              <p>Printing a variable alongside text with multiple arguments works, but the spacing gets awkward.</p>
              <Code code={Figure2} frame="code" lang="javascript" showLineNumbers={false} />
              <p class="fragment">Output: <code>You scored 95 %.</code> &mdash; notice the extra space before the <code>%</code>.</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>Template Literals</h2>
              <p>
                A backtick string becomes a <b class="text-sn-theme">template
                literal</b> the moment you drop a variable inside
                <code>{"${ }"}</code>.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure3} frame="code" lang="javascript" showLineNumbers={false} />
              <p class="fragment">Output: <code>You scored 95%.</code> &mdash; exactly the spacing you wrote.</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>Interpolating Expressions</h2>
              <p>
                <code>{"${ }"}</code> isn't just for variables &mdash; it can
                hold any expression, like a calculation.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure4} frame="code" lang="javascript" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Today's Objectives</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Writing template literals with backticks</li>
                <li>Interpolating variables into a string with <code>{"${ }"}</code></li>
                <li>Interpolating expressions into a string</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Terms</h2>
              <div class="text-start">
                <dl>
                  <dt>Template Literal</dt>
                  <dd>A backtick-quoted string that can have values dropped directly inside it.</dd>
                  <dt>Interpolation</dt>
                  <dd>Inserting a variable or expression's value directly into a string.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </section>
          </Presentation>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Build -->
        <section id="build">
          <h2>Build</h2>

          <p>
            Create a new JavaScript file named <b class="text-sn-theme">1-6-interpolation.js</b>.
          </p>

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 1: Interpolate a Variable</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Declare a <code>score</code> variable.</li>
            <li>Print it once with multiple <code>console.log()</code> arguments, and once with a template literal.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task1} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-6-interpolation.js" mark="4" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 2: Interpolate Multiple Variables</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Declare <code>name</code> and <code>age</code> variables.</li>
            <li>Interpolate both into a single template literal.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task2} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-6-interpolation.js" mark="9" ins="6-9" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 3: Interpolate an Expression</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Write a template literal that interpolates an arithmetic expression directly, not just a variable.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task3} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-6-interpolation.js" mark="11-12" ins="11-12" />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Checkpoint -->
        <section id="checkpoint">
          <h2>Checkpoint</h2>

          <p>Verify your program works correctly.</p>

          <Code
            code={SampleOutput}
            frame="terminal"
            lang="txt"
            showLineNumbers={false}
            title="Example Output"
          />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Reflection -->
        <section id="reflection">
          <h2>Reflection</h2>

          <p>Answer the following questions before submitting your work.</p>

          <ol>
            <li>What symbol turns a normal backtick string into a template literal with a value inside it?</li>
            <li>Why did the multi-argument <code>console.log()</code> version have an extra space that the template literal version didn't?</li>
            <li>Besides a plain variable, what else can go inside <code>{"${ }"}</code>?</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Submit -->
        <section id="submit">
          <h2>Submit</h2>

          <p>Submit the required files to the appropriate dropbox.</p>

          <h1
            class="text-center mt-5 text-sn-theme border border-primary slow-flash"
          >
            Activity Complete
          </h1>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
